Samples of Al, Ti, Co, Zr, Nb, Ag, in, Nd, Sm and Ta
elements in contact with solid-state nuclear track
bremsstrahlung beams at the 2.5 GeV electron
synchrotron of the Bonn University. The detectors
were processed to produce visible fission tracks for
track analysis with optical microscopes. Absolute
mean cross sections per photon and fissility were
evaluated. Results are discussed and compared with
other photofission data as well as with estimates
from the current fission models. A broad minimum
covering the range Z**2/A = 15 - 25 seems to confirm
the predictions from the models. For Al and Ti
nuclei the probability of fission amounts to about
